21/8/15
Arabs sitting there playing backgammon. Past old mosque lit by gas floors heavily carpeted and doctors expounding Koran to groups around them. No admission on account of holy day. 
Bought tarboush at stall. Seller wanted PI 20 but beat him down to PI 5.
Returned by tram at 7 pm. Tea and then to Gordon House at 8.15 to meet J. Waited for a while as on day duty and did not come off until 8 o'clock. To Hotel and took gharry for obelisk after usual bargaining. Closed at 25 piastre. Had ideal drive in moonlight through Zeitoun and village between green irrigated fields of cotton and flax and dwellings. The villagers in groups singing, many lying